n gsay, even if some were in areas that others couldn't reach (we brought spells down to our non-luclin folks as well).  This system will *completely remove* those with economic means from the rest of us unwashed rabble, potentially changing the psychosocial environment of the game substantially.  Also, one of the big 'selling points' for the expansions to a new EQ player is the encouragement of friends they make in the game, telling them about what lies beyond what they currently have.  With this type of setup, that link will also be gone, providing yet more evidence that Verant is perfectly willing to 'kill the goose that lays the golden eggs' by cutting its subscriber pipeline off at the point of entry.  Or perhaps they've crunched the numbers and decided that a few new subscribers at 40.00/mo is worth watching their 10.00's/mo dwindle down to nothing?<br><br>Sincerely,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective<br><br>P.S.  There were fewer than 100k subscribers online (on Friday night!) when I checked the site.  It was 160k in non prime time just a few months ago, *prior* to luclin release.  Wonder when or if we will start to see server merges?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/unenabierdieb.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nena Bierdieb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/2/02 1:45:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=884.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: VERANT SUCKS StuPID MONKEY ASS!</span><hr size=1> Considering the number of people who maintain multiple accts, I wonder if they'll really see the numbers they think they will.  For our house to move to that server, we'd be paying not 40 a month, but 120 a month, and there are others I know who would be paying a lot m